dcterms:description: AffectNet is one of the largest datasets for facial expression recognition, containing a substantial number of images collected from the internet, annotated with facial expressions, valence, and arousal. It allows for the analysis of demographic biases in facial expression recognition models.
dcterms:title: Affectnet
